                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	Chennai, June 20: Tamil Nadu police have arrested three suspected LTTE operatives from Tamil Nadus Tiruchi.           
	The police have seized 4,900 ordinary detonators and 430 electric detonators from Siva, Selvam and Thamizh. The trio had been staying illegally in India. They had procured the detonators locally to smuggle them to Sri Lanka.                   
	 Dehra Dun (PTI): At least six tourists were assaulted by policemen, who were allegedly drunk, in Mussoorie, sparking protests in the hill resort. The four cops, who allegedly got involved in a scuffle with the group of tourists at Mall Road in Mussoorie on Saturday night, were transferred on Sunday. The cops also beat up the tourists with batons.                  
	Vadodara (PTI): Five lions slipped out of the Gir sanctuary yesterday afternoon and were seen on a nearby village road.The lions did not attack passers-by, who did not panic either. The lions were on their way to the nearby Shetrunji river to quench their thirst, a forest official said.                  
	Hyderabad (PTI): A mentally unsound woman allegedly drowned her 45-day-old baby girl in a water-filled bucket , police said. Sujatha had herself called the police but was arrested after her husband D. Sriramulu, a labour contractor, alleged that she might have killed the baby.                  
	Muzaffarnagar (PTI): A community panchayat has served an ultimatum to the family of a boy who has eloped with a minor girl to return the child to her parents within a day, police said. The whereabouts of the couple are not yet known.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): Delhi police will launch a drive to educate people against possible terror threats and seek public support in checking crime ahead of the Commonwealth Games. The police will spend over Rs 20 crore this year on the awareness drive , which is double the amount they had spent in 2009-10.                                                                                                                                              
